&gt; 
&gt; I brought the following thought up elsewhere and will bring it up 
&gt; here for consideration, too.  If ghosts are coming through the box 
&gt; and thus are not in a good state of mind, how come on Paranormal 
&gt; State CM was willing to believe the message given by the ghost via 
&gt; the box as being truth (The ghost via the box said a &quot;demon&quot; was 
&gt; holding the ghosts captive there)?  
&gt; 
&gt; I would suggest that perhaps a ghost (assuming we are talking about 
a 
&gt; disembodied person who remains earthbound) is not in a healthy 
state 
&gt; of mind one would consider &quot;stable,&quot; but trapped in emotional 
trauma 
&gt; of some sort.  Thus, how reliable could the message of a ghost then 
&gt; be?  ;)
&gt; 
&gt; LC
